  "html": "<h1>Applies to</h1>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>Microsoft® Windows Communication Foundation (WCF) 3.5 \r\n<li>Microsoft Visual Studio® 2008</li></li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n  <h1>What to Do</h1>\r\n  <p>If you need to publish your WCF service metadata, consider publishing it over HTTPS Protocol. </p>\r\n  <h1>Why</h1>\r\n  <p>This allows you to protect your clients from being spoofed when adding a service reference. </p>\r\n  <h1>When</h1>\r\n  <p>Consider using this guideline when your clients&nbsp;need&nbsp;to refer your&nbsp;service.</p>\r\n  <h1>How</h1>\r\n  <p>Publish your service metadata over Secure HTTP (HTTPS) to protect clients from being spoofed when adding a service reference. Clients cannot be certain that they have added a reference to the right service if you expose your service metadata over HTTP. The service may have been spoofed through Domain Name System (DNS) poisoning or a man-in-the-middle attack.</p>\r\n  <p>To publish your service metadata over HTTPS, use <strong>mexHttpsBinding</strong> and configure a server certificate for the service. </p>\r\n  <h1>Additional Resources</h1>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>For more detailed steps, see “How to: Secure Metadata Endpoints” at <a href=\"http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms733114.aspx\">http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms733114.aspx</a><li>For more information on publishing metadata, see “Publishing Metadata“ at <a href=\"http://msdn2.microsoft.com/en-us/library/aa751951.aspx\">http://msdn2.microsoft.com/en-us/library/aa751951.aspx</a><li>For more information, see “Security Considerations with Metadata” at <a href=\"http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms734741.aspx\">http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms734741.aspx</a><br /></li></li></li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n  <hr />\r\n  <p>Adapted from Microsoft patterns & practices guidance.</p>"
